CaMa-Flood

```json
{
  "application": "CaMa-Flood",
  "software_requirements": [
    "Fortran",
    "OpenMP",
    "Intel compiler and libraries (optional)",
    "NetCDF library (optional)",
    "PBS (optional)"
  ],
  "resource_requirements": {
    "cpu": "20",
    "memory": "10gb",
    "storage": "dependent on input/output data sizes"
  },
  "input_data": [
    "runoff forcing (plain binary or netCDF)",
    "river map (plain binary or netCDF)",
    "restart file (optional)"
  ],
  "output_data": [
    "river flow and storage (plain binary or netCDF)",
    "restart file (optional)"
  ],
  "additional_notes": [
    "The script provides options for different forcing and map data formats.",
    "The script includes features for spin-up and restart simulations.",
    "The script is designed for running on a high-performance computing cluster (HPC) using PBS.",
    "The script requires specific environment variables to be set, including: IFORTLIB, DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH, and OMP_NUM_THREADS."
  ]
}
```
